ord+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2005-09&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Foed.com%2Fsearch%3FsearchType%3Ddictionary%26q%3Dplus&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAddition" class="Z3988" about="#mwt63" id="mwA7g"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt63" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA7k"/><span typeof="mw:Entity" about="#mwt63" id="mwA7o"> </span><span style="font-size:0.95em; font-size:90%; color:#555" about="#mwt63" id="mwA7s">(Subscription or <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.oxforddnb.com/help/subscribe#public" id="mwA7w">UK public library membership</a> required.)</span></span></li><li about="#cite_note-15" id="cite_note-15"><a href="./Addition#cite_ref-15" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-15" class="mw-reference-text">See Viro 2001 for an example of the sophistication involved in adding with sets of "fractional cardinality".</span></li><li about="#cite_note-16" id="cite_note-16"><a href="./Addition#cite_ref-16" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-16" class="mw-reference-text"><i id="mwA70">Adding it up</i> (p. 73) compares adding measuring rods to adding sets of cats: "For example, inches can be subdivided into parts, which are hard to tell from the wholes, except that they are shorter; whereas it is painful to cats to divide them into parts, and it seriously changes their nature."</span></li><li about="#cite_note-17" id="cite_note-17"><a href="./Addition#cite_ref-17" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-17" class="mw-reference-text">Mosley, F. (2001). <i id="mwA74">Using number lines with 5–8 year olds</i>. Nelson Thornes. p. 8</span></li><li about="#cite_note-18" id="cite_note-18"><a href="./Addition#cite_ref-18" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-18" class="mw-reference-text">Li, Y., &amp; <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Glenda_Lappan" title="Glenda Lappan" id="mwA78">Lappan, G.</a> (2014). <i id="mwA8A">Mathematics curriculum in school education</i>. Springer. p. 204</span></li><li about="#cite_note-19" id="cite_note-19"><a href="./Addition#cite_ref-19" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-19" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt87" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"Taschenbuch der Mathematik"},"author-first1":{"wt":"Ilja Nikolaevič&lt;!-- Nikolajewitsch -->"},"author-last1":{"wt":"Bronstein&lt;!-- 1903–1976 -->"},"author-first2":{"wt":"Konstantin Adolfovič&lt;!-- Adolfowitsch -->"},"author-last2":{"wt":"Semendjajew&lt;!-- 1908–1988 -->"},"editor-first1":{"wt":"Günter"},"editor-last1":{"wt":"Grosche"},"editor-first2":{"wt":"Viktor"},"editor-last2":{"wt":"Ziegler&lt;!-- 1922–1980-->"},"editor-first3":{"wt":"Dorothea"},"editor-last3":{"wt":"Ziegler"},"others":{"wt":"Weiß, Jürgen&lt;!-- lector -->"},"translator-first":{"wt":"Viktor"},"translator-last":{"wt":"Ziegler"},"volume":{"wt":"1"},"date":{"wt":"1987"},"edition":{"wt":"23"},"orig-year":{"wt":"1945"},"publisher":{"wt":"[[Verlag Harri Deutsch]] (and [[B.G. Teubner Verlagsgesellschaft]], Leipzig)"},"location":{"wt":"Thun and Frankfurt am Main"},"language":{"wt":"German"},"chapter":{"wt":"2.4.1.1."},"pages":{"wt":"115–120"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-3-87144-492-0"},"title-link":{"wt":"Bronstein and Semendjajew"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA8E">Bronstein, Ilja Nikolaevič; Semendjajew, Konstantin Adolfovič (1987) [1945]. "2.4.1.1.".  In Grosche, Günter; Ziegler, Viktor; Ziegler, Dorothea. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" hre